  <header>
    <h1>Strawberry Bars</h1>
    <a href="../index.html">← Back to Home</a>
  </header>

  <main>
    <img src="../images/strawberry-bars.jpg" alt="Strawberry Bars" class="full-recipe-img">

    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>1 cup butter, softened</li>
      <li>1 cup sugar</li>
      <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
      <li>1/4 tsp salt</li>
      <li>1/2 cup strawberry jam</li>
      <li>1 cup chopped fresh strawberries</li>
      <li>Powdered sugar for dusting (optional)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Instructions</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease an 8x8 inch baking dish.</li>
      <li>In a bowl, cream butter and sugar. Mix in flour and salt until crumbly.</li>
      <li>Press 2/3 of the mixture into the bottom of the pan.</li>
      <li>Spread jam over the crust. Top with chopped strawberries and sprinkle remaining crust mixture.</li>
      <li>Bake for 35–40 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely and dust with powdered sugar if desired.</li>
    </ol>
  </main>

